		<p>
			They say the most common time of year to gain weight 
			is between Christmas and New Year, where the festive
			season seems to encourage gluttony and abandon of our
			fitness goals.
			We've all been there -- we've all experienced the
			post-Christmas dinner food comas that somehow lasts for
			days and the champagne-hangovers that causes us to wake
			up with a cringe.  
			We've felt how easy it is to fall out of our exercise
			routines whilst on holiday, and we've all made
			those resolutions to get fitter, healthier, and leaner
			for the coming year.
			Thus I present Winter Detox Smoothie, the perfect
			recipe to detox your bad habits and help kick-start
			your healthier lifestyle.
		</p>
