		<h3> 
			Only Protein (paleo product review) 
		</h3>
		<p>
			Since hearing about the paleolithic diet, I've been
			experiemting with various paleo products and recipes.
			Albeit a bit extreme, overall I think it's a sound
			approach to nutrition, emphasising lean meats, healthy
			fats, and vegetables whilst limiting starches and all
			processed-foods. 
			However, I was concerned to hear protein powder did not
			count as paleo, until I found
			<a href="https://www.onlyprotein.com/">
				Only Protein</a>
		       &#8211; the only pelo whey protein powder. 
			I was lucky to recieve free samples from the company,
			and used the vanilla protein powder in this recipe.
			What can I say about this product? Aside from being
			slightly too sweet and rather difficult to get a hold
			of, it's probably one of the best and purest protein
			powders on the market.  Their slightly higher prices
			are justified by the
			quality of their ingredients, and I would highly
			recommend this to anyone looking for a pure whey
			protein powder!
		</p>
